> Personally I think Evade should be effected by haste like Backstab is.  <br><br>Another solution would be RapidEvade as an AA skill like Rapid FD. <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=66715"<b><font size="5">Pokn<BR></font></b></a>60th Assassin of Tholuxe Paells<BR><a href="http://kupoflux.com"><IMG SRC="http://www.netdesign.net/~kitae/kupo.jpg"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulordvaghrisbloodreaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lord Vaghris Bloodreaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/30/02 7:53:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: evade success, needs upgrade, thoughts?</span><hr size=1> I agree on that, evade is starting to leave my grp with lom clerics while i soak up mana acting as tank.  I dont even have that great of a weapon (trak tooth) and i STILL out agro the tanks, even if backstab fails.  Gah, i wonder how much longer im going to be acting as the MA =P<br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Edit: Please read our sig/personal pic rules. - ShadowCross</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ushadowcross.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shadowcross</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_purplespot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 3/31/02 2:04:10 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujlailyvarkas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jlaily Varkas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/30/02 9:18:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: evade success, needs upgrade, thoughts?</span><hr size=1> FabCorpse, I don't want evade to be easier, I want it to be proportionately successful to backstabs and procs<br><br><br>Bayler,  the /pause seems very viable, as soon as I get home from work today I am adding that to my hotkey, especially with this new queue crap so we don't loose messages, I have seen at least a 3 second delay on anything, specific example rezzes, now I have the rez effects before I get loading please wait, I really hate the new queueing for messages<br><br>so far the proc is not an agro problem, if evade works most of the time<br><br>I also love the ideas that evade is affected by haste = overall faster refresh, <br><br>maybe we could get a gradual evade refresh time reduction as you lvl, like sneak run speed goes up as you lvl, near full run speed at lvl 60 when sneak<br><br>or a quick refreshing evade as AA<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uprodigious.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Prodigious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/30/02 9:25:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: evade success, needs upgrade, thoughts?</span><hr size=1> i think evade rate is fine, but /agree vaslin &amp; pokn. great ideas.<br><br>and I think we should be able to evade persistently, because about the only thing a rogue brings to a high-end raid is damage. no spells, no pulling, no tanking. so let us do damage all the way. <p><font size="2" face="Arial"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21797">Veteran Prodigious</a><br>Assassin<br>Fennin Ro</font><br><img src="http://prod.homepage.dk/pics/1106bs.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udeeleeryous.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deeleeryous</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/31/02 4:39:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: evade success, needs upgrade, thoughts?</span><hr size=1> Personally, I think Evade is fine. Parsing my log reveals that it is successful about 68% of the time. It is enough for me to virtually never get agro. Sure, I am not using a NTOV weapon, but I still do around 70-75 dps.<br><br>Could it be better? Sure could. Does it need to be? Not IMHO. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=153133" style="color: #FFFF00"><font face="Arial" size="3">Deeleeryous Doljonijiarnimor</font></a><BR><b>Redeemed Assassin of The Nameless</b><BR>Proud member of <i>Valorguard</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uravenwingedangel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravenwinged Angel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/31/02 9:04:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: evade success, needs upgrade, thoughts?</span><hr size=1> Well some of us do 70-75 damage a hit.  Factor into that how many hits we do a second and you can see why evade doesn't really cut the mustard.<br><br>I think it's parculiar that evade works just as good for me at level 3 as it does at level 60.<br><br>It would have been nice if the success rate of evade was tied into the Hide skill somehow.  Especially considering that Hide goes up to 200 for rogues, and yet, always succeeds once you have 100 skill.  So what is the point of that extra 100 points of hide anyway?<br><br>Barring that, an AA ability that makes Evade always succeed(assuming your not moving) would be nice as well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urunetheborrower.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rune the Borrower</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/1/02 12:43:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: evade success, needs upgrade, thoughts?</span><hr size=1> Evade needs to be upgraded, hell, it needs to just plain work too.<br><br>Tonight in the grey I was grouped with a 59 ranger, a 59 pally, a 55ish SK, a 55 rogue and a 60 cleric. On one of the snakes I evaded &quot;SUCCESSFULLY&quot; 3 straight times and it NEVER looked at anyone else. I'm not even well equipped. (Ragebringer and Rapier of Oriin) No procs to cause extra agro, health wasn't low and no disc was used.<br><br>What's up with that? <p>Runehammer Trollsbane<BR>Assassin of Cazik-Thule<BR><BR>Runesword<BR>Shadowblade of Gawain<BR>"I yam what I yam."<BR>Popeye</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ustixum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stixum</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/1/02 5:10:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=20>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: evade success, needs upgrade, thoughts?</span><hr size=1> Personally I think failing evade 14 times in a row is BS and yes it needs a minor bit of tuning.  Sometimes I will have a streak where I will evade 9 out of 10 times, then I will have a streak where I will fail 19 out of 20 times.  I would think that a lvl 60 rogue would have a better success rate then someone 10-20 levels lower then him/her, but the success rate remains unchanged no matter what lvl you are.<br><br>Just my 2cp <p><p><table><tr><td style ="filter:glow(color= #00ff00 strength=5); color: #000000; font-family:arial; font-weight:bold; font-size:'10pt'"> Baron Stixum Fogerty <br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=998  target="web"> 60 Gnome Assassin </a> </td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utobyl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tobyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/1/02 9:49:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: evade success, needs upgrade, thoughts?</span><hr size=1> Evade is only a small part of agro control.    Procing weapons are a big factor but probably the most important thing is letting your tank get some agro before you engage.  On uber mobs, if you dont let your tanks gain agro for at least a few seconds before you start poking I can gaurantee you that you will out agro them.  During normal grinds, give your tank maybe 2-3 seconds just to let him hit taunt first and get a few hits in.<br><br>Procs also play a role and some weapon procs agro alot more than others.  If you have a Willsapper and a SoD youre going to get agro.  Salindrite Dagger and a Smoulder and youve got a bit less chance.<br><br>The other thing to keep in mind is who is pulling.  Its at least twice as hard (for me anyway) to lose agro if I was the one pullling the mob.<br><br>Evade is fine the way it is, I only ever get agro on certain mobs and even then only under awkward circumstances, such as Dain catapulting all the tanks, tanks dying, etc.  What  needs to be looked at is the stupid rampage list.<br><br>Tobie Baine<br>Assassin<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showMessageRange?topicID=23086.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showMessageRange?topicID=23086.topic&start=41&stop=59>3</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showNextMessage?topicID=23086.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=21><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.emailToFriend?topicID=23086.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> 